-------------------------------------------------------------------------
D. SystemVerilog Testbench Description
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

The  top-level testbench is written in SystemVerilog. The SPI interfaces 
are represented as instances of 'interface' objects. The hdl_interconnect 
is represented as a SPI model with 'interface' connections as its ports.
The UVM verification environment is represented as an spi_basic_env instance.
The test file is created as a class which extends spi_base_test.

The file containing the top-level testbench in the example is "top.sv".  
This file which encapsulates individual tests is "top_test.sv".

The SPI model used in the example is defined as a hdl_interconnect, within a SystemVerilog
wrapper. The intent is to demonstrate how a legacy core may be integrated into
the SystemVerilog testbench.


The SystemVerilog wrapper for the SPI model defines a module that takes 'interface'
references as its port connections. The SystemVerilog wrapper instantiates
the Verilog SPI bus model, and connects SPI MASTER and SLAVE interfaces to the SPI model.

The example SPI bus model is found in the file "hdl_interconnect.v". The example wrapper
is found in the file "spi_svt_interconnect_sv_wrapper.sv".

The entire UVM test environment is encapsulated in spi_basic_env.sv, which is
instantiated in the UVM tests.  The tests gets included in 'top.sv',
which eventually triggers the specific test by the use of run_test().

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
E. UVM Verification Environment Description
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

A complete description of the UVM environment (ENV) is beyond the scope of this
README. Please refer to the UVM manual for details of a UVM environment.

Following is a summary of the files used by the ENV:

  - spi_svt_interconnect_sv_wrapper.sv.  A SystemVerilog module that wraps the
    verilog RTL Interconnect.  This will be instantiated in the top-level SystemVerilog
    file.
  
  - spi_basic_env.sv
    This file serves as environment class.  The top-level environment is
    implemented by extending uvm_env base class.  This class instantiates the
    SPI MASTER and SLAVE agents and a virtual sequencer.

  - cust_svt_spi_agent_configuration.sv
    This file extends agent configuration (svt_spi_agent_configuration).
    All the necessary configuration parameters are set up for the environment
    in this class.

  - cust_svt_spi_transaction.sv
    This file extends the transaction (svt_spi_transaction).
    Customized constraints are defined by this class.

  - spi_simple_reset_sequence.sv
    This file shows a virtual sequence that generates a simple sequence
    to drive the reset pins.  This sequence is registered with the TB
    virtual sequencer as the default sequence for the reset phase.

  - spi_default_virtual_sequence.sv
    This file implements a virtual sequence executes an
    spi_default_sequence on MASTER and SLAVE agent sequencer.  This sequence is registered with the 
    SPI ENV virtual sequencer as the default sequence for the main
    phase.

  - spi_null_virtual_sequence.sv
    This file implements a virtual sequence with an empty body method.  This
    sequence can be used by extended tests to disable the default sequence.

  - spi_default_sequence.sv
    This file shows a sequence (extending from uvm_sequence)
    that generates a default random svt_spi_transaction.

